{
  "stem": "449.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Here comes the affidavit, but in the meantime, I was in Marseilles, and the war started.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have the paper.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Every citizen of the Reich had to appear, with food for one day, and clothes, to go in the prison camp, because being a citizen of the Reich, he had to be-- so I didn't feel like a citizen of the Reich because I am Austrian.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I came with an Austrian passport.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "No, I came to Turkey with an Austrian passport, but when I wanted to go out of Turkey, Austria was already occupied.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So there was no Austria.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I had to take a German passport, and I came with the German passport to Marseilles, which made me a citizen of the Reich.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I ignored it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I am not a German.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't have to listen to the orders that the citizens of the Reich had to do.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the police somehow knew there were many Jewish refugees who are in the same condition, who are Austrian, but really they were not Austrian and they are not Germans.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So what they did to do to get them all we had the [NON-ENGLISH] HIAS took care of us, gave us a room to live, gave us food, and we had to go to the soup kitchen.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Every day, to the soup kitchen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one day when I went with my oldest son-- my wife that day stayed in the hotel with the other kid, and I went alone with him.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there the police had arrested all the Jews in the soup kitchen who were with a German passport.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I had the kid.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They arrested me with the kid, and nobody could leave the hall.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the meantime, my wife heard about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
